# Components

## Folder layout

One folder per component, named in PascalCase:

```
src/components/Button/Button.tsx
src/components/Button/Button.test.tsx
```

Export from `src/components/index.ts`:

```typescript
export { default as Button } from './Button/Button';
```

## Implementation

- Default-export the component; wrap with `memo()` when props are stable.
- Import theme tokens from `@/theme` — no hardcoded colors, spacing, or font sizes.
- Use the shared `Text` component instead of React Native's `Text` for typography.
- Set a `testID` prop with a sensible default (e.g. `button-view`, `button-text`).

```typescript
// ❌ BAD
padding: 12,
backgroundColor: '#3366FF',

// ✅ GOOD
import { colors, spacing, border, text } from '@/theme';

padding: spacing.xs,
backgroundColor: colors.palette.primary400,
borderRadius: border.radius,
```

## Tests

Co-locate `ComponentName.test.tsx`. Render via `@/utils/test` and query by `testID`.

```typescript
import { fireEvent, render } from '@/utils/test';
import Button from './Button';
```
